post_text: Proposition Vote is TODAY! Voting is now underway through 7 PM tonight. Voters are being asking to decide whether to keep a PK-8 grade school open in the community and close only the high school--or close the school entirely. A yes vote keeps a school in the community; a no vote shuts down the school.
shared_text:
Panola Public Schools
June 22 at 8:02 PM ·

If you are a registered voter in the Panola School District and vote at one of the precincts listed below, you will receive a ballot concerning the proposition of making Panola School a PK-8 school. The vote is set for Tuesday, June 30th. (Early voting begins this Thursday, June 25th.)

post_text: We know that many of you in our community have questions about the upcoming vote on June 30th. What does this mean for our school? Our new superintendent, Mr. Bryan Deatherage, would like to answer as many of your questions as possible. [The Panola School Board has hired Mr. Deatherage as a shared superintendent with Red Oak.] Because we cannot safely hold a large community meeting [due to COVID-19], we are asking that you send us your questions so that he can address them via social media ahead of the proposition vote. Please DM the Panola Public Schools' Facebook page or email your questions to: terry.broyles@panolabearcats.org

Beginning Monday, teachers will be contacting parents to see which ones have internet and which ones do not.

Many have contacted the school regarding personal items belonging to students. You may contact the office between the hours of 8:00 am and 12:00 pm, Monday thru Thursday to schedule a time to pick up items. The dates for pick up will be April 6-April 16. We are all trying to figure this out together. Thank you for you patience and understanding during this unprecedented time.

post_text:
During this unprecedented time, Panola Public School is preparing for the continuing education of your child. There will be a State Board of Education meeting tomorrow, March 25th. We will receive instruction on how to proceed after that meeting. We are not able to conduct any instruction until April 6th. Our staff will be meeting this week to plan for the remainder of the year. Your child’s teacher will be reaching out the week of April 6th in order to provide lessons. We will have a plan in place and will communicate that plan to you as soon as possible. We will keep you updated as we receive information. At this point, we know that Superintendent Hofmeister has requested school attendance be wavered until the end of the year. Also, state testing will not take place this year. I know several have asked about 8th grade reading tests for driver’s licenses. There are alternative tests available at our school that will suffice for the reading test. Please know that we are on top of the situation and have your child’s education as a priority.

I hope you stay healthy!
Stacey Votravis

Parents/Guardians:
On Friday, March 16, Panola School lost Jewelie Bullard, a teacher, a friend, and a colleague. Mrs. Bullard had been battling an illness for the last few months and finally succumb to the battle she had so gallantly fought. Her funeral service is on Tuesday, March 20 at 2:00 at the Wilburton School Auditorium. Because of Mrs. Bullard's dedication to Panola School and to the students we are not having school on that day (Tuesday) to honor our colleague.
Sincerely,
Brad Corcoran

post_text:
2017-2018 PRE-ENROLLMENT FOR PRE-K THROUGH 12TH

JULY 17-19, JULY 25-27, JULY 31
8 AM to 3 PM

Pre-kindergarten students must be 4 by September 1, 2017.
Kindergarten students must be 5 by September 1, 2017.

ALL STUDENTS MUST PRE-ENROLL BY AUGUST 1st.

Enrollment will be completed online in the ELEMENTARY BUILDING for ALL GRADES.

If you need to enroll after hours, please call the office at (918) 465-0011 EXTENSION 2 to make other arrangements.

Please BRING the following information to enroll:

*BIRTH CERTIFICATE (new students only)
*IMMUNIZATION RECORD (new students only)
*SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER (for each child)
*CASE NUMBER (if applicable)
*CDIB CARD (if applicable)

The enrollment process will take between 15-20 minutes for each student. If you do not come with the information listed above, you will not be able to complete enrollment and will have to return at another time.

post_text: School can be different. Panola Public Schools would love the opportunity to serve your child in the coming 2017-2018 school year. Panola will have an individual learning plan for each of our students, offering a personalized program that is customized to meet the needs of your child. Students will use cutting edge technology in a safe and friendly environment that is committed to EVERY child succeeding and learning. If you're interested, the time to act is now to guarantee that you are able to transfer into our school. The state deadline is May 31. Please call 918-465-6188 NOW to ensure your transfer is approved. If your child is struggling in school, being picked on, bullied or simply needs a change, please give us the opportunity to serve your family and help.

In honor of READ ACROSS AMERICA Panola Elementary has 3 days of fun activities planned besides the reading goals set by each classroom teacher for their students.

▪Wednesday - Students will meet in the activity room to show off their "foxy" crazy socks. Mr. Corcoran will read "Fox in Socks" and students will take the Reading Oath. "Cat in the Hat" parfaits will be enjoyed at break recess.
▪Thursday - Buddy reading between the classes and "Cat in the Hat"cupcakes will be served at break recess in honor of Dr. Seuss' birthday.
▪Friday - Pajama day [only for those students who met their reading goal] and the movie "Horton Hears A Who" with Hop on Pop- corn for the snack.
